user_query:
I’m preparing a concise research brief for our CTO on a few fast-evolving topics. Please do the following:

1) Read input/topics.json for the list of topics and constraints (minimum/maximum results per topic, time window, and language). Also read input/exclude_domains.txt for domains to exclude and input/style_guide.md for formatting guidance for the summary.

2) For each topic, perform broad web searches across general, news, and scientific/technical sources. Gather 5–8 high-quality, recent links (within the time window in input/topics.json). Make sure each topic has at least one news article and at least one scientific/technical source. Deduplicate strictly by URL. Exclude any results whose domain appears in input/exclude_domains.txt.

3) Create these outputs under the output/ folder:
- output/sources.json — A structured JSON with this shape:
  {
    "metadata": {
      "generated_at": "ISO8601 timestamp",
      "total_topics": <int>,
      "total_links": <int>,
      "unique_domains": <int>
    },
    "topics": [
      {
        "topic": "<topic string>",
        "results": [
          {
            "title": "<string>",
            "url": "<http(s) URL>",
            "source_type": "news|science|general|docs",
            "engine": "<string> (may be empty if unknown)",
            "date": "<ISO8601 or empty if unknown>",
            "snippet": "<1–2 sentence summary>"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
- output/citations.csv — A CSV with columns: topic,title,url,source_type,domain,engine. One row per result in sources.json.
- output/summary.md — A readable brief that follows input/style_guide.md. Include a short intro, then a section per topic (use headings like “## <topic>”) with a curated top 5 list of links, each as a bullet point with a citation-style link and a 1–2 sentence annotation explaining its relevance and key takeaway.

4) Be careful to: respect the time window, ensure domain diversity per topic, include the required mix of source types, and avoid the excluded domains. Keep all content in English.

Write only to the specified files in output/ and make sure the JSON and CSV are well-formed.
